title: China’s top diplomat to visit D.C. amid tensions over South China Sea, Israel
description: Officials in Washington hope that talks with China’s Foreign Minister Wang Yi could see Beijing use its influence to pressure Iran not to join the Israel-Hamas fight.

title: West Bank militancy surges as Israel steps up raids and arrests
description: Israel’s escalating raids and arrests in the West Bank are an extension of its war against Hamas in Gaza, but analysts say the crackdown could fuel militant activity.

title: Tropical storms and hurricanes still roam the Atlantic and Pacific
description: Forecasters are monitoring Hurricane Tammy in the Atlantic while Otis is set to become the fourth tropical storm to make landfall in Mexico this month in the Pacific.

title: Israeli forces raid inside Gaza, step up air strikes, killing hundreds
description: Airstrikes hit across the Gaza Strip, including in the southern areas the IDF told Palestinians to evacuate for their own safety.

title: ‘The Empty Grave of Comrade Bishop’: Podcast episode guide
description: An episode guide: Grenada’s Prime Minister was executed in a coup in 1983. The location of his remains is unknown. New details reveal the role the U.S. played.

title: Ukrainian spies with deep ties to CIA wage shadow war against Russia
description: The CIA has built up Ukraine’s espionage capabilities, but U.S. officials stress that the agency has no involvement in targeted killings operations by Kyiv

title: Brazil blames U.S. pilots in crash that killed 154. They’re still flying.
description: The question of responsibility for the 2006 Gol Flight 1907 crash, then Brazil’s deadliest aviation disaster, divided the Western Hemisphere’s largest nations.

title: A store let customers steal shoes — if they could outrun a pro sprinter
description: Distance, a Paris running store, told customers they could steal items if they outran the security guard: Méba Mickael Zeze, one of France’s fastest sprinters.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Second aid convoy enters Gaza; U.S. braces for regional escalation
description: Fourteen trucks entered Gaza on Sunday, but the U.N. aid chief warned that Palestinians need “much more” help as the humanitarian crisis deepens.

title: Israel’s bombing of Gaza undercuts the West’s Ukraine moralism
description: Politicians and diplomats are seeing American greenlight in Israel’s pounding of Gaza, and call into question an apparent double standard that President Biden’s rhetoric can’t mask.

title: Venezuelans back candidate to challenge Maduro — if she’s allowed
description: The authoritarian socialist government has promised a competitive presidential election next year, but opposition nominee María Corina Machado has been barred from running.
